e was taken from the first letters of each founders surname contents  history  timeline  other acquisitions  other past units  references  external links historyedit loral corporation originally worked on developing radar and sonar detection methods for the us navy in  it went public with an initial offering of  shares at  each part of the proceeds from this offering were used to build a new headquarters on its acre  m site at  bronx river avenue in the soundview section of the bronx new york in  it began to diversify buying several smaller companies through which it won more military contracts some purchased companies included willor manufacturing corp american beryllium co inc of sarasota florida arco electronics and several plastics companies in  it formed a division for developing communications telemetry and space navigation systems for satellites as its expansion and buying other companies increased it borrowed  million from the massachusetts mutual life insurance company in  in the late s it was awarded many military contracts including a  million us navy contract for doppler navigation radar in  a  million contract from general dynamics for advanced electronics for the us air force f airplane in  and a  million contract for airborne countermeasures for the phantom rfc reconnaissance plane by the late s loral specialized in radar receivers which identified signatures of enemy radar systems on missiles and antiaircraft guns however by the late s lorals corporate purchases were causing problems for the company by  it had lost  million and was sometimes unable to meet its loan payments many acquisitions were not profitable and also not in lorals primary business the founders lorenz and alpert were prepared to sell half their interest in the company loral was on the verge of bankruptcy in  before it was acquired by bernard l schwartz who over the course of the next two decades built it into a major player in the global aerospace and defense industry acquiring  other defense and aerospace companies in  loral had  billion in revenue in  loral sold its defense electronics and system integration businesses to lockheed martin its remaining units became loral space  communications the following year several of those former loral units were spun off by lockheed martin to become the core of l communications loral was accused of transferring technology to china in  the incident arose as a result of an investigation into the launch failure of intelsat  a space systemsloral–built satellite in a  agreement with the state department and department of justice the company agreed to pay  million in fines to settle the matter and to improve its compliance procedures in the agreement loral officials neither admitted nor denied the governments charges but loral executives acknowledged the nature and seriousness of the offenses alleged by the department in the draft charging letter including the risk of harm to the security and foreign policy interests of the united states and stated that they wished to make amends through the payment of restitution schwartz subsequently released a statement accepting full responsibility for the matter and portrayed the incident as an error by a single loral employee timelineedit  loral electronics corporation founded  loral makes a public stock offering and becomes a public corporation  loral is on the verge of bankruptcy bernard l schwartz acquires it  goodyear tire and rubber company sold goodyear aerospace corporation gac to loral which became loral defense systems october  loral acquires ford aerospace the divisions of which become space systemsloral and loral western development labs  with qualcomm loral begins the globalstar project and at the peak owns a  share in the company  loral acquires ibms federal systems division which becomes loral federal systems may   loral acquires paramax the defense unit of unisys for  million in cash january   lockheed martin agreed to purchase the defense electronics and system integration businesses of loral for  billion loral becomes loral space and communications october   loral space  communications inc and the public pension investment board of canada received the final regulatory approval necessary to complete the acquisition of telesat from bce inc for cad  billion the acquisition closed on october   with loral owning  percent of telesat other acquisitionsedit fairchildweston ltv missiles solartron other past unitsedit loral aeronutronic rancho santa margarita california loral command control systems loral conic san diego california loral defense systems akron ohio loral instrumentation san diego loralliris loral rolm milspec computer systems san jose california loral space information systems loral space  range systems sunnyvale california loral terracom san diego loral vought systems grand prairie texas now part of lockheed martin missiles and fire control loral narda loral randtron loral western development laboratories loral infrared  imaging systems liris lexington massachusetts loral electro optical systems leos pasadena california referencesedit new york city portal companies portal  loral space  communications ltd stocklobster retrieved  may    loral corporation encyclopediacom retrieved  may    securities and exchange commission news digest april   cf p on lorals ipo  powell focuses the spotlight on a guarded military plant new york times tuesday april    satellite maker fined  million in china trade secrets case new york times thursday january    marx v loral corporation caseawfindlawcom  june  retrieved  may  goodyear sold gac to loral corporation “loral” in march  after which loral became the plan administrator and fiduciary   peltz jeff f  january  lockheed will buy loral corp for  billion los angeles times retrieved  may  lockheed martin corp seeking to dramatically alter the landscape of the defense industry for the second time in less than a year said monday that it has agreed to buy the defense electronics 